        <!-- Architecture -->
        <div class="project-section alt-bg">
            <h3>Architecture Explanation</h3>
            <p>The VPC architecture implements enterprise networking patterns:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>VPC (10.0.0.0/16)</strong> – Private virtual network isolating all resources.</li>
                <li><strong>Public Subnet (10.0.0.0/24)</strong> – Internet-facing resources with public IPs.</li>
                <li><strong>Private Subnet (10.0.1.0/24)</strong> – Internal resources without public IPs.</li>
                <li><strong>Internet Gateway</strong> – Enables public subnet to reach the internet.</li>
                <li><strong>NAT Gateway</strong> – Allows private subnet outbound internet access securely.</li>
                <li><strong>Public Route Table</strong> – Routes 0.0.0.0/0 → Internet Gateway.</li>
                <li><strong>Private Route Table</strong> – Routes 0.0.0.0/0 → NAT Gateway.</li>
                <li><strong>Bastion Host</strong> – Secure jump box for accessing private instances.</li>
                <li><strong>Custom NACL</strong> – Subnet-level firewall for additional security.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

