            <p>
                This project covers enterprise VPC design patterns:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Always place <strong>databases and backend servers</strong> in private subnets.</li>
                <li>Use <strong>NAT Gateway</strong> (not NAT Instance) for production workloads.</li>
                <li>Implement <strong>bastion hosts</strong> or AWS Systems Manager for secure access.</li>
                <li>Apply <strong>least-privilege Security Groups</strong> at instance level.</li>
                <li>Use <strong>NACLs</strong> as an additional layer for subnet-level control.</li>
                <li>Enable <strong>VPC Flow Logs</strong> for network traffic monitoring.</li>
                <li>Consider <strong>VPC Endpoints</strong> for private access to AWS services.</li>
            </ul>
